    "content": "✅ Approved the contribution.\nComment: Creative: Using letter case to encode three states (laughing/maybe/sullen) is a good idea, and the two-step simultaneous update good enough challenge. Many \"Easy\" problems are trivially single-pass tho.\nGood test coverage: The test suite is thorough: edge cases for lonely people, sullen blockers, duo/trio, distance limits, and the equidistant tie-break. That's a good aproach.\nThe tie-break rule is clever: Taking the closest letter from each side (closest_laughing[0][1] + closest_laughing[1][0]) is original.\n\nI like it enough so approve ;)",
